Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uuildiienea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uildiienea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/23/02 4:33:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1568.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The EQ Begger</span><hr size=1> To me it depends on how they ask.<br>
My hot key informs them that their skill in begging has not increased. <br>
<br>
The very irritating n00b at the NFP bank last night, who asked at least 10 people in the few minutes I was there  &quot;got anything for a new player&quot;   Ignore.<br>
<br>
But one night someone sent me a request <br>
<br>
N00b &quot;Could I have a moment of your time?&quot; <br>
I &quot;Yes, what can I assist you with&quot;<br>
N00b &quot;I hate to ask, but could I possibly borrow 116PP to purchase spells&quot;<br>
<br>
I knew at lvl 4 spells did not cost 116PP, but I loaned him the PP, put him on my friends list, mainly out of curiousty - to check his progress etc. <br>
<br>
2 weeks later I get a tell from him &quot;I have the PP that I borrowed from you now&quot; <br>
<br>
Lvl 18 now. I commended him on his honesty, and told him that I did not want the PP back - I wanted him to continue his EQ adventures showing the integrity that he had shown to me. Some how I have a feeling he will do just that. <br>
<br>
Having them collect 40 batwings for PP - to me it isn't slave labor. It is rewarding them for hard work. <br>
<br>
When I first started there was a high lvl wizzard in Gfay offering 5PP per stacks of batwings. To me it was fun - my first armor purchased with rewards of my efforts - it was leather, but it was good for me - then. When I &quot;grew up&quot; I would cast sow, etc on him everytime our paths crossed. <br>
<br>
The worst zone for begging I have noticed lately - EC. God I hate even passing through there. <br>
<br>
<br>
Uildiienea Yorrkeagle<br>
51 Druid<br>
Officer of Infinite Void <br>
