<br>Nibl Heim, 53 Cavalier<hr></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukdor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kdor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/24/02 10:52:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1568.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The EQ Begger</span><hr size=1> My response to beggars has changed over time.  I used to donate a few gold or copper or whatever I had on me.  Unless it was a warrior.  Then I would chastise them as degrading our profession and they should consider being a Ranger.  Now I usually use my hotkey with &quot;NO Beggars!  Begone!  Or feel the wrath of my blade!&quot;  It usually startles them enough to leave.<br>
<br>
<br>
I also made a tidy sum farming bear pelts and silks and crap as a newbie in Everfrost.  One necro gave me 800 pp over time suppying him with bone chips.  He over paid greatly, but he always had a steady supply, and he offered.  I also was paid 40pp per HQ pelt if I collected 10 or more.  So, I agree its a good thing for newbs to do, as I stopped gaining exp for a month just to earn a little cash to start out with.<br>
<br>
Last but not least, I have to admit I am guilty of starting a character, leveling them to 2 or 3 in a few minutes, then proceed to beg the HELL out of my friends and guildees, just to see their reactions.  I have a mischivous character and I love teasing people, and I have had quite a few chuckles doing this.  No, I never take anything offered as I always say it sucks and I want more/better etc.  LOL.  Yeah, if this sounds familiar, it was probably me trying to rile you.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><CENTER>
